==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Onslaught
<hw>On"slaught`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>on</ets>
on + <ets>slaught</ets>, <ets>slaht</ets>, slaughter. See
<er>Slaughter</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An attack; an onset; esp., a
furious or murderous attack or assault.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By storm and <qex>onslaught</qex> to proceed.</q>
<rj><qau>Hudibras.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bloody fray or battle.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Onstead</ent>⟦br⟧
